  "text": "Cervical cancer is a common malignancy, aetiologically associated with infection by a group of human papillomavirus (HPV) types. Previous studies have shown a striking DLG1 overexpression in cervical precursor squamous intraepithelial lesions (SILs). In these samples DLG1 was lost from cell contacts and redistributed to the cytoplasm, especially in the high-grade SILs [CITATION_1] Cavatorta et al., 2004) .",
